### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

See this example

```ts
import { Component, signal } from '@angular/core';
import { bootstrapApplication } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { form, FormField, email } from '@angular/forms/signals';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  imports: [FormField],
  template: `
    <input [formField]="userForm.email" />
    <p>invalid: {{ userForm().invalid() }}</p>
    @for(error of userForm().errors(); track $index ){
      <ul>
        <li>{{ error.message }}</li>
      </ul>
    } @empty {
      <p>NO ERROR</p>
    }
  `,
})
export class App {
  protected readonly user = signal({ email: 'foo' });
  protected readonly userForm = form(this.user, (schemaPath) => {
    email(schemaPath.email, {
      message: 'Invalid email',
    });
  });
}

bootstrapApplication(App);
```

The output: 

```
foo
invalid: true
NO ERROR
```

the expected output is
```
foo
invalid: true
Invalid email
```

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackblitz-starters-veekyw2p

### Please provide the environment you discovered this bug in (run `ng version`)

```true
Angular 21.1.2
```

Otherwise a component can be held in memory longer than the component constructor is reachable from application code.

